{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"878f6693-5fbc-41a7-bcc0-19355691b676","content":"Here's the skip attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod, Ignore(\"Waiting on bug #1234 fix\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Flaky on CI\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test, Ignore(\"Needs database migration\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test, Skip(\"Blocked by upstream API\")]\npublic async Task MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nAll four frameworks will report these as **skipped** (not failed) in test results, with the reason visible in the output.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0b1653c1-4b5d-4c5f-a8d3-8c9ec83f10a9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the correct attributes to skip tests with a reason message in MSTest, xUnit, NUnit, and TUnit. Let me provide a concise answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":310,"requestId":"1BC2:28B932:6C5A222:74DCBC0:6A03D24C"},"id":"8c7c20b7-6df4-41e5-a3a1-61ac1401fdf7","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:22:27.248Z","parentId":"5403572a-eff0-45ca-884d-b6aee5ae1728"}
